4. 

# Partition (Training Dataset : Test Dataset = 7:3)
y      <- UB.df$Personal.Loan                            # Target
 
set.seed(200)
ind    <- createDataPartition(y, p = 0.7, list = T)      # Index  7:3 
UB.trd <- UB.df[ind$Resample1,]                          # Training Dataset
UB.ted <- UB.df[-ind$Resample1,]                         # Test Dataset

5.

Package "caret" API R . Package "caret" (Grid Search), (Random Search), . degree, scale, C (Cost) , . .

fitControl <- trainControl(method = "cv", number = 5,  # 5-Fold Cross Validation (5-Fold CV)
                           allowParallel = TRUE,       #  
                           classProbs = TRUE)          # For   

set.seed(100)                                          # For CV
svm.po.fit <- train(Personal.Loan ~ ., data = UB.trd, 
                    trControl = fitControl,
                    method = "svmPoly",
                    preProc = c("center", "scale"))    # Standardization for

1) Package pROC

pacman::p_load("pROC")

svm.roc  <- roc(ac, pp, plot = T, col = "gray")          # roc( class,  )
auc      <- round(auc(svm.roc), 3)
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")

Caution! Package "pROC" ROC .

#  plot.roc() 
plot.roc(svm.roc,   
         col="gray",                                     # Line Color
         print.auc = TRUE,                               # AUC  
         print.auc.col = "red",                          # AUC  
         print.thres = TRUE,                             # Cutoff Value  
         print.thres.pch = 19,                           # Cutoff Value   
         print.thres.col = "red",                        # Cutoff Value   
         auc.polygon = TRUE,                             #     
         auc.polygon.col = "gray90")                     #    

#  ggroc()

3) Package ROCR

pacman::p_load("ROCR")

svm.pred <- prediction(pp, ac)                           # prediction( ,  class)    

svm.perf <- performance(svm.pred, "tpr", "fpr")          # performance(, "", "1-")                      
plot(svm.perf, col = "gray")                             # ROC Curve

perf.auc   <- performance(svm.pred, "auc")               # AUC
auc        <- attributes(perf.auc)$y.values 
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")
